div.p:
Q. BUt what if notwithstanding all your present Desires, and Resolutions, you should chance to fall away from your Duty; and thereby put your self out of this state of Salvation; 
   •
s there no way left for you to recover your self, and to return again to it?

                  A. It was: For the Wages of Sin is Death:
                  Isa. liii.10. 1 Pet. i.18, 19. Rom. vi.23. and without shedding of Bloud there could be no Remission: Heb. ix.22. And therefore we could not have been deliver'd from Death, on any other Terms, than by Christ's dying in our stead. Whereas by dying,Rom v.10. viii.32. Col. i 21. He has made a full Satisfaction for our Sins;




has taken away the Sting of Death; And conquer'd him who had the Power of Death, that is, the Devil. Heb. ii.14. ix.x. Rom. v.6, 8. 1 Cor. xv.55, 57.
